President Obama spoke with President Putin of Russia to discuss several important issues. They emphasized the need for a diplomatic solution to the crisis in Ukraine, specifically through the full implementation of the Minsk agreements. They also discussed the importance of reaching an agreement on the modalities of local elections in the Donbas region of Ukraine. Additionally, the leaders talked about the urgent need to implement United Nations Security Council Resolution 2254 on Syria and the necessity of fostering productive discussions between representatives of the Syrian opposition and regime. They highlighted the importance of reducing violence and addressing the urgent humanitarian needs of the Syrian people. Lastly, they discussed the need for a strong and united international response to North Korea's nuclear test, which defied Security Council resolutions.